1. SALES PROCESS OVERVIEW
=========================

Our sales process follows a structured 6-stage approach:

Stage 1: QUALIFY (0-10% probability)
- Initial outreach response received
- Basic fit confirmed (company size, industry)
- Key activities: Research, initial call scheduled
- Exit criteria: Discovery call completed

Stage 2: DISCOVER (10-25% probability)
- Pain points identified and quantified
- Stakeholder map started
- Key activities: Discovery calls, needs assessment
- Exit criteria: Business case outline agreed

Stage 3: DEMONSTRATE (25-50% probability)
- Tailored demo delivered
- Technical validation started
- Key activities: Demo, trial setup, technical Q&A
- Exit criteria: Champion confirmed, positive demo feedback

Stage 4: PROPOSE (50-75% probability)
- Proposal delivered
- Commercial terms discussed
- Key activities: Proposal presentation, negotiation
- Exit criteria: Verbal agreement on terms

Stage 5: NEGOTIATE (75-90% probability)
- Contract redlines in progress
- Procurement engaged
- Key activities: Contract negotiation, security review
- Exit criteria: Final terms agreed

Stage 6: CLOSE (90-100% probability)
- Signature pending or obtained
- Key activities: Contract execution, handoff to CS
- Exit criteria: Signed contract received

