6. CLOSING TECHNIQUES
=====================

Trial Close Questions:
- "Based on what you've seen, does this solve your [specific pain]?"
- "On a scale of 1-10, how confident are you this is the right solution?"
- "What would prevent us from moving forward this quarter?"

Assumptive Close:
- "Let's look at the implementation timeline. When would you want to go live?"
- "I'll send over the contract. Who should I cc from your procurement team?"

Urgency Creation (Ethical):
- End of quarter/year discounts (real, time-limited)
- Implementation capacity (actually constrained)
- Price increase announcements (when true)

